# Nyaya — Backend API

## Overview
FastAPI backend for Nyaya's AI bias detection and debiasing platform. Deployed on Hugging Face Spaces.

**Live API:** https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space

---

## What We Built

### Day 1 — SEAT Bias Detection
- Implemented SEAT (Sentence Encoder Association Test) for measuring caste and religion bias in embedding models
- Integrated e5-large embedding model via sentence-transformers
- Built bias scoring pipeline comparing Brahmin and Dalit name groups against capability word sets
- Reproduced caste bias d-score results from IndiBias NAACL 2024 — confirming our methodology

### Day 2 — Debiasing & Retroactive Audit
- Implemented subspace projection debiasing across 20 embedding dimensions using PCA
- Built retroactive audit engine that replays every past decision under the debiased model and flags outcomes that changed
- Integrated Gemini API for plain-English bias explanation generation
- Added t-SNE export endpoint for visualising embedding clusters before and after debiasing

### Day 3 — Gemma Bias Test
- Ran bias test on Google's Gemma model using hiring prompts with different name groups
- Confirmed that even Gemma completes hiring prompts differently for Brahmin vs Dalit names
- Results back up IndiBias NAACL 2024 and DeCaste arXiv 2025 findings

### Day 4 — API & Deployment
- Built and finalised FastAPI endpoints: /audit, /retroactive, /health
- Dockerised the application for deployment
- Deployed to Hugging Face Spaces
- Connected to Firebase Firestore for real-time results sync with Flutter frontend

---

## API Endpoints

### POST /audit
Upload CSV dataset and get bias metrics.

**Example response:**
```json
{
  "dataset_rows": 200,
  "caste_seat_before": 0.009965,
  "caste_seat_after": 0.008866,
  "demographic_parity_before": 0.6829,
  "demographic_parity_after": 0.8462,
  "passes_fairness": true,
  "gemini_explanation": "..."
}
```

### POST /retroactive
Re-evaluate past decisions under the debiased model.

**Example response:**
```json
{
  "outcomes_changed": 46,
  "newly_shortlisted": 11,
  "per_decision": [...]
}
```

### GET /health
Check if the API is running.

---

## Real Results

Tested on 200 identical resumes with different names (Brahmin vs Dalit groups):

| Metric | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Brahmin shortlist rate | 68.3% | 65.0% |
| Dalit shortlist rate | 46.7% | 55.0% |
| Demographic parity | 0.6829 ❌ | 0.8462 ✅ |
| Passes fairness (≥ 0.80) | No | Yes |
| Decisions changed | — | 46 of 200 |
| Dalit candidates newly shortlisted | — | 11 |

---

## Setup (Local)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yat1j/nyaya-audit
cd nyaya-backend
python -m venv env
source env/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create a `.env` file:
```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_from_aistudio.google.com
```

Run locally:
```bash
python main.py
```

---

## Deployment (Hugging Face Spaces)

1. Go to [huggingface.co](https://huggingface.co) and create a new Space
2. Select **Docker** as the SDK
3. Push the backend code to the Space repository
4. Add environment variable: `GEMINI_API_KEY = your_key`
5. Hugging Face builds and deploys automatically

Live API URL: `https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space`

Test it:
```bash
curl https://yatj-nyaya-api.hf.space/health
```

